    "sections": {
        "description": "<p>XO Post Background is a plugin to set background image and color for each post.</p>\n<p>Background image details (size, position, etc.) and background color can only be set in WordPress 5.7 or higher block editors.</p>\n",
        "installation": "<ol>\n<li>Upload the <code>xo-post-background</code> folder to the <code>/wp-content/plugins/</code> directory.</li>\n<li>Activate the plugin through the Plugins menu in WordPress.</li>\n</ol>\n",
        "changelog": "<h4>2.0.11</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Enabled to fix the position of the background image in iOS Safari.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.0.10</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed an issue where non-admin users could not save posts when setting the background.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.0.9</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed a bug that an error message may be displayed in the pattern editor.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.0.8</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed a bug that the editor may get an error when selecting a gradation.</li>\n<li>Supported WordPress 6.3.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.0.7</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed background image scaling issue on iOS Safari.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.0.5</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed PHP 5.6 compatibility issue.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.0.4</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed a bug that the background color was not reflected.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.0.3</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Supported transparency in background color.</li>\n<li>Fixed a bug that caused error messages to appear in the editor for custom posts that do not support custom fields.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.0.2</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added gradient option to background color.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.0.1</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Fixed a bug that was not translated.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4>2.0.0</h4>\n<ul>\n<li>Added options such as setting the position of the background image and the background color.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><a href=\"https://xakuro.com/wordpress/xo-post-background/#changelog\" rel=\"nofollow ugc\">See the previous changelogs here</a></p>\n"
    },
